The paper deals with the problem of diversified top-k search, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) systems. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes algorithms for solving the problem, which involves techniques from data structures (DS), artificial intelligence (AI), and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.DS, cs.AI, and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories.
